Q1. Red Packet Sharing at Grandma’s House

# During Chinese New Year reunion dinner in Singapore, Grandma prepares $88 to give equally to 3 grandchildren in red packets.
# Each grandchild must receive the same whole-dollar amount, and no one should receive less than their fair share.

# Write a program that asks for the total amount of money and number of grandchildren, then displays how much each grandchild receives in one sentence.


# Q2. Chinatown Firecracker Purchase

# A family visits Chinatown to buy firecrackers for Chinese New Year.
# Each box of firecrackers costs $12.80.
# There is a 10% festive discount, but after the discount, a fixed $1.50 GST charge is added to the total bill.

# Write a program that asks for the number of boxes bought and prints the final amount payable, rounded to 2 decimal places.


# Q3. Pineapple Tart Container at Home

# At home, a family prepares pineapple tarts for visiting relatives.
# A container can hold up to 2.5 kg of pineapple tarts.
# Each pineapple tart weighs 0.18 kg.

# Write a program that calculates and displays the maximum number of pineapple tarts that can be placed into the container.


# Q4. Lion Dance Drum at the Community Centre

# During a Chinese New Year celebration at a Singapore community centre, a circular lion dance drum is used.
# The radius of the drum (in cm) is given by the user.

# Write a program that calculates and displays the area of the drum in square centimetres, rounded to the nearest whole number.


# Q5. Chinese New Year Zodiac Greeting

# In 2026, a student is curious about their age during Chinese New Year.
# The student enters their birth year.

# Write a program that calculates the student’s age in 2026 and displays a Chinese New Year greeting stating the age and whether the age is an even or odd number.
